{
  "_comment": [
    "WIN-SYS-009 -- safe mode, crash recovery and profile recovery.",
    "Composition-PINNING contract (calc-chrome style) over the seven real upstream",
    "recovery / Safe-Mode surfaces and their two weld consumers. These are weld",
    "GtkDialogs whose Material look is produced entirely by shared vcl parts already",
    "declared in definition.xml (windowbackground/BackgroundDialog, pushbutton",
    "Entire+Focus, checkbox, radiobutton, progress TrackHorzArea+Entire, frame/Border)",
    "rendered behind VCL_FILE_WIDGET_THEME -- there is no recovery-specific draw code",
    "to add. The honest, build-free M-scope is therefore to PIN the .ui composition so",
    "the row's core constraint (these safeguards must remain INTACT, never removed or",
    "rerouted) is enforced fail-closed, to PIN the two weld consumers so the source",
    "keeps binding the preserved widgets, to GROUND the treatment in the named native",
    "parts (resolvable in both the light and dark palettes), and to RECONCILE (read",
    "only) the seven KeepModal policy rows plus the shared no-nag retained safeguards.",
    "",
    "It is source evidence only: runtime_verified is false throughout -- no native",
    "build, dialog pixels, or runtime interaction are claimed. The Material dialog",
    "anatomy (16px sheet, scrim, title row, destructive @error-container emphasis on",
    "Discard All) and the Discard-All -> sfx2::ConfirmDestructiveAction conversion are",
    "build-dependent behavioural changes carved out below with status 'specified'; the",
    "safe-default invariant is already satisfied build-free by the existing has-default",
    "on the safe action.",
    "",
    "Cross-references are read-only: qa/windows-ui-contract/dialog-notification-policy.csv",
    "is owned/validated by check-windows-dialog-notification-contract.py and the no-nag",
    "retained-safeguard markers by check-windows-no-nag-contract.py; this contract never",
    "mutates either, it only asserts the seven recovery rows stay native-exclusion and",
    "the three recovery safeguards survive."
  ],
  "schema_version": 1,
  "contract": "material-recovery-safemode-composition",
  "platform": "windows",
  "definition_file": "vcl/uiconfig/theme_definitions/material/definition.xml",
  "policy_registry": "qa/windows-ui-contract/dialog-notification-policy.csv",
  "theme_flag": "VCL_FILE_WIDGET_THEME",
  "status": "source-declared",
  "runtime_verified": false,
  "design_reference": "docs/design/08-dialogs.md (8.6 recovery/crash/Safe Mode), docs/design/07-feedback.md (7.1 recovery progress)",
  "dialogs": [
    {
      "id": "docrecoveryrecoverdialog",
      "ui_file": "svx/uiconfig/ui/docrecoveryrecoverdialog.ui",
      "dialog_id": "DocRecoveryRecoverDialog",
      "widget_class": "GtkDialog",
      "action_widgets": [
        { "response": "-6", "id": "cancel" },
        { "response": "101", "id": "next" }
      ],
      "required_widgets": [
        { "id": "next", "class": "GtkButton" },
        { "id": "cancel", "class": "GtkButton" },
        { "id": "desc", "class": "GtkLabel" },
        { "id": "filelist", "class": "GtkTreeView" },
        { "id": "progress", "class": "GtkProgressBar" }
      ],
      "safe_default": {
        "default_action": "next",
        "forbidden_default_actions": ["cancel"],
        "reason": "Recover Selected (response 101) must stay the Enter default; Discard All (response -6) must never become the default."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "docrecoverysavedialog",
      "ui_file": "svx/uiconfig/ui/docrecoverysavedialog.ui",
      "dialog_id": "DocRecoverySaveDialog",
      "widget_class": "GtkDialog",
      "action_widgets": [
        { "response": "-5", "id": "ok" }
      ],
      "required_widgets": [
        { "id": "ok", "class": "GtkButton", "properties": { "has-default": "True" } },
        { "id": "filelist", "class": "GtkTreeView" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "docrecoverybrokendialog",
      "ui_file": "svx/uiconfig/ui/docrecoverybrokendialog.ui",
      "dialog_id": "DocRecoveryBrokenDialog",
      "widget_class": "GtkDialog",
      "action_widgets": [
        { "response": "-5", "id": "ok" },
        { "response": "-6", "id": "cancel" }
      ],
      "required_widgets": [
